pageContext.claim: “We have the strongest economy anywhere in the world, by far.”
pageContext.analysis: The United States has the biggest economy but "strongest" is dubious. The American economy expanded at an annual rate of 3.5 percent in the third quarter of 2018. But China's gross domestic product growth, at 6.6 percent, is still almost  double U.S. growth even as its economy slows down. Many other countries has faster growth rates, including India, Latvia, Poland and Greece. Many analysts believed the U.S. economy started to slow in the 4th quarter.
